In a message dated 12/26/02 10:06:44 PM Central Standard Time, 
wingedwarrior41@... writes:


&gt; Belthassan&#39;s reply to her stare was equally cold. It was getting
&gt; obvious he didn&#39;t like her.
&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan: Oh? Then let me update history. The Great Wars are over.
&gt; Megatron and Optimus Prime are both dead. Your time is gone. You said
&gt; it yourself: no other Decepticon made it to this age... at least, not
&gt; without the upgrade to Maximal or Predacon. Thus, I say that the likes
&gt; of you are dead. Now shut up, listen, watch and learn.

She growled as her optics narrowed. She didn&#39;t like that. She didn&#39;t like 
that at all. Being treated like a stupid old bot. 

&gt; 
&gt; He stood up and went close to an old wire cable sticking out of the
&gt; ground. It was old but still strong and big.
&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan: Melchana, please make it so we can show what we&#39;re able to do.
&gt; 
&gt; The lioness came near and, in one movement of her arms, slashed the
&gt; wire in three pieces. She threw them all in the air.
&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan shot a freezing ray of ice at one piece and punched it with
&gt; a huge fist, shattering it in dozens of pieces.
&gt; 
&gt; Melchana aimed at one with both arms at fired a hail of sandy
&gt; particles which eroded to piece to nothing in moments.
&gt; 
&gt; Gesper lashed out with his tail and ensnared the last piece. It seemed
&gt; to do nothing but there soon was a crackling of static and the smell
&gt; of something burning. When he let go, the fried wires fell smoking to
&gt; the ground.
&gt; 
&gt; Belthassan: That is only a fraction of what we can do. Once you can
&gt; transform, you&#39;ll be able to use it too. Now the question is the same
&gt; one our first ancestors asked each other: Friend or Foe?
&gt; 

She was largely unimpressed. &#39;A tiny little wire was the only example they 
could make?! Pathetic!&#39; she thought. In her days, they would make use of huge 
buildings, or enemies, perhaps worlds as target practices for their weapons. 
Now THAT was impressive, & she admitted it. 

&quot;I don&#39;t make friends, only allies & comrades.. IF they are to my liking or a 
benefit.&quot; She paced a moment. &quot;However, I am willing to put this all aside & 
assist. I was once a Decepticon Dignitaries Aide, you know. Of course, I am 
sure ALL the old codes are gone by now. Hmm.. but allas, I am unable to 
perform my rightful duties in this form.&quot; Stating with such drama. 

Soon enough turning serious. &quot;Very well, I will assist you in what you need, 
IF,&quot; raising a clawed paw, &quot;you assist me in regaining my old body back.&quot; 

Her optics went to those who call themselves transformers. She would never 
break a promise.  

